              <DefinitionShort>to bring about a mutually accepted agreement between two or more parties, with the probable additional component of making something certain</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to bring about an agreement</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to cause an agreement</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Since one who was a {L:μεσίτης&lt;SDBG:μεσίτης:000000&gt;} ({D:31.22}) often acted as one who provided the surety or guarantee of an agreement or arrangement, there is a significant component of certainty involved in μεσιτεύω. Hence, one may understand this as implying not only the agreement but the guarantee of its validity.</Comments>
